3.11 Risks & Mitigations
Risk	Probability	Impact	Mitigation
Lab infrastructure costs spiral	High	High	Start with lightweight Docker labs, not full VMs. Aggressive auto-shutdown. Spot instances. Set per-user concurrent lab limits. Monitor cost per active user obsessively.
Dynamic lab generation is technically hard	High	High	Start with "semi-dynamic" — 10 variants per lab template, randomly assigned. Build toward fully procedural generation over time.
Content production bottleneck	Medium	High	Hire experienced cybersecurity content creators. Build authoring tools that reduce friction. Eventually open community contributions (curated).
TryHackMe/HTB copy the model	Medium	Medium	Move fast. Build community moat. Brand loyalty. They're large and slow to change core architecture. Our advantage is being purpose-built for this from day 1.
Low free → paid conversion	Medium	High	Ensure free tier gives enough value to hook, but clear limitations that create upgrade desire. The first lab in every path is free + first look at adaptive difficulty.
Security of lab environments	Medium	Critical	Network isolation per user (K8s network policies). No internet access from labs (or restricted). Regular security audits of orchestration layer. This is a cybersecurity platform — if we get hacked, we're dead.
Cohort instructor quality	Medium	High	Rigorous vetting process. Standardized curriculum (instructors augment, not create from scratch). Student feedback loops.
Scaling too fast	Low	Medium	Waitlist + invite codes to control growth in early months. Scale infrastructure ahead of user growth.
